1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:01,556
(Previously)
Why didn't you wake me up last night?

2
00:00:01,580 --> 00:00:02,926
You literally passed out.

3
00:00:02,951 --> 00:00:04,000
How could I wake you up?

4
00:00:04,357 --> 00:00:05,565
You're definitely sulking.

5
00:00:06,124 --> 00:00:07,809
I was exhausted last night.

6
00:00:07,857 --> 00:00:08,897
I really was.

7
00:00:10,679 --> 00:00:13,380
Why is trying to do something
for the person you love

8
00:00:13,783 --> 00:00:15,160
so exhausting?

9
00:00:15,866 --> 00:00:17,600
Is a rescuer like me not good enough?

10
00:00:17,836 --> 00:00:19,480
If you have to try this hard for love,

11
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,600
does it really make sense?

12
00:00:23,831 --> 00:00:25,904
I think I'm going to ask for some space.

13
00:00:26,046 --> 00:00:27,074
Don't be paranoid yet.

14
00:00:27,119 --> 00:00:28,200
You just started dating.

15
00:00:28,347 --> 00:00:29,580
Exactly.

16
00:00:29,798 --> 00:00:32,038
Maybe it'll hurt less to end it sooner
rather than later.

17
00:00:32,409 --> 00:00:33,800
I'm not letting you leave me!

18
00:00:34,039 --> 00:00:35,039
I'll fight!

19
00:00:35,619 --> 00:00:36,720
I'll fight for us!

20
00:00:37,761 --> 00:00:39,121
I said I'd fight.

21
00:00:39,531 --> 00:00:41,480
I've decided to step into this battlefield.

22
00:00:41,893 --> 00:00:43,240
I'm a dog barking at a plane.

23
00:00:43,429 --> 00:00:44,549
I'm a fighter.

24
00:01:05,416 --> 00:01:06,416
Kanit!

25
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,240
Are you okay?

26
00:01:09,339 --> 00:01:10,339
Kanit!

27
00:01:35,427 --> 00:01:36,427
Toto.

28
00:01:54,256 --> 00:01:55,256
Ow!

29
00:01:59,171 --> 00:02:01,677
Why are you hugging me?

30
00:02:03,717 --> 00:02:05,760
I thought you died
and rotted away in your room.

31
00:02:06,599 --> 00:02:09,079
You didn't pick up the phone.
You didn't answer when I knocked.

32
00:02:09,824 --> 00:02:10,824
I won't die.

33
00:02:11,452 --> 00:02:12,572
I'm just sick.

34
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:18,880
Whoa, you're burning up.

35
00:02:19,298 --> 00:02:20,406
Have you seen a doctor yet?

36
00:02:21,057 --> 00:02:23,280
I wanted to, but I didn't
have the energy to drive.

37
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,720
Why didn't you call me? I can take you.

38
00:02:27,211 --> 00:02:30,111
You're going to catch
my cold after that hug.

39
00:02:30,267 --> 00:02:32,522
I won't. I'm strong.

40
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:33,965
I have a great immune system.

41
00:02:35,748 --> 00:02:36,853
But I'm worried about you.

42
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,600
"A Dog and A Plane"
(Episode 9)

43
00:03:56,994 --> 00:03:59,783
ONLY THE DETERMINED WILL WIN

44
00:03:59,898 --> 00:04:01,160
You have a lot of tattoos.

45
00:04:01,499 --> 00:04:02,619
Didn't it hurt getting them?

46
00:04:02,722 --> 00:04:03,749
It's just like love.

47
00:04:05,174 --> 00:04:06,001
It hurts,

48
00:04:06,142 --> 00:04:07,142
but it's beautiful.

49
00:04:13,574 --> 00:04:14,270
What?

50
00:04:14,303 --> 00:04:15,888
I just want to keep looking at your face.

51
00:04:15,912 --> 00:04:17,320
Are you playing a lovestruck guy?

52
00:04:18,183 --> 00:04:18,989
I love you.

53
00:04:19,046 --> 00:04:19,762
I love you.

54
00:04:19,787 --> 00:04:20,351
I love you.

55
00:04:20,376 --> 00:04:20,939
I love you.

56
00:04:20,974 --> 00:04:21,551
I love you.

57
00:04:21,582 --> 00:04:22,582
- I love you.
- Enough.

58
00:04:23,286 --> 00:04:24,760
Enough. Why do you keep saying that?

59
00:04:24,946 --> 00:04:26,000
Because I want to.

60
00:04:27,631 --> 00:04:28,324
Hey.

61
00:04:28,418 --> 00:04:29,560
Promise me one thing.

62
00:04:30,253 --> 00:04:33,160
From now on, you have
to tell me everything, okay?

63
00:04:34,719 --> 00:04:36,573
No sulking or overthinking
things on your own.

64
00:04:37,571 --> 00:04:38,996
Is there anything
you want to tell me right now?

65
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:40,320
Hmm…

66
00:04:40,651 --> 00:04:43,880
I forbid you from going to work tomorrow.

67
00:04:44,669 --> 00:04:45,669
Hmm?

68
00:04:46,634 --> 00:04:47,819
I'm taking you on a date.

69
00:04:49,778 --> 00:04:50,297
A date?

70
00:04:50,370 --> 00:04:52,954
To make up for how little
we've seen each other lately.

71
00:04:53,813 --> 00:04:55,480
I know you're exhausted from work.

72
00:04:55,986 --> 00:04:57,280
I want you to relax.

73
00:04:57,853 --> 00:05:02,280
I'm going to go hard.

74
00:05:04,143 --> 00:05:05,143
I like hard.

75
00:05:19,762 --> 00:05:21,306
♪ Huy lay hui, ha ha ♪

76
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:23,126
♪ Huy lay hui, hey hey ♪

77
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:24,682
♪ Huy lay hui, ha ha ♪

78
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,361
♪ Huy lay hui, hey hey ♪

79
00:05:27,606 --> 00:05:29,210
♪ Hey, let's try it, hey ♪

80
00:05:29,248 --> 00:05:30,321
♪ Let's fight it ♪

81
00:05:30,346 --> 00:05:31,119
Arms to the side.

82
00:05:31,144 --> 00:05:33,987
♪ Don't get worn out now, hey, let's push it ♪
Hey.

83
00:05:34,321 --> 00:05:35,770
You might as well
not even look at the instructor.

84
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:37,162
You're just making up your own moves.

85
00:05:37,186 --> 00:05:38,240
I can't focus anymore.

86
00:05:38,572 --> 00:05:39,960
How can you even keep up?

87
00:05:40,314 --> 00:05:42,114
This is even more exhausting
than rescue work.

88
00:05:43,648 --> 00:05:45,547
I thought you said
this was going to be a romantic date.

89
00:05:45,571 --> 00:05:48,471
That's exactly why I
brought you to work out.

90
00:05:48,635 --> 00:05:50,680
You have to take better
care of your health.

91
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:52,680
Where would I find the time?

92
00:05:52,854 --> 00:05:53,854
I have to work.

93
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:55,160
Then I have to eat.

94
00:05:55,232 --> 00:05:56,234
Then I have to find time to sleep.

95
00:05:56,258 --> 00:05:57,572
And then I have to wake up for work again.

96
00:05:57,596 --> 00:05:58,640
It's a neverending loop.

97
00:05:59,282 --> 00:06:02,671
If you keep this up,
you're going to cut your life short.

98
00:06:02,746 --> 00:06:04,679
What? Why are you jinxing me?

99
00:06:04,994 --> 00:06:06,243
I'm not.

100
00:06:06,534 --> 00:06:08,440
But you have to work out

101
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:09,960
so you can live a long life

102
00:06:10,593 --> 00:06:12,202
and be with me for a long time, got it?

103
00:06:17,957 --> 00:06:19,680
So that's why you brought me to work out?

104
00:06:19,956 --> 00:06:20,956
Yeah.

105
00:06:21,287 --> 00:06:22,287
Come on.

106
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,650
You're more romantic than I thought.

107
00:06:24,674 --> 00:06:26,615
Why are you hugging me?
There are lots of people here.

108
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:27,760
We're supposed to squat.

109
00:06:28,156 --> 00:06:28,775
Go!

110
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,431
Okay.

111
00:06:29,525 --> 00:06:31,040
I can keep dancing for another hour.

112
00:06:31,219 --> 00:06:32,720
So I can be with you for a long time.

113
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:35,080
I can do this for another hour.

114
00:06:36,411 --> 00:06:37,625
Bring it on, coach.

115
00:06:37,744 --> 00:06:38,744
So I can…

116
00:06:39,001 --> 00:06:40,481
So I can be with you for a long time.

117
00:06:41,278 --> 00:06:41,995
- Come on.
- Come on, everyone.

118
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:42,995
So I can be with you for a long time.

119
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:43,606
Jump!

120
00:06:43,631 --> 00:06:44,631
Let's go!

121
00:07:01,332 --> 00:07:01,969
Hey.

122
00:07:02,013 --> 00:07:03,013
Turn this way.

123
00:07:03,091 --> 00:07:04,091
Hmm?

124
00:07:09,695 --> 00:07:11,520
This will make you look handsome.

125
00:07:11,638 --> 00:07:12,238
What?

126
00:07:12,352 --> 00:07:13,680
Am I not handsome right now?

127
00:07:14,118 --> 00:07:17,291
You're already handsome,
but you'll get even more handsome.

128
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:20,440
Any more handsome than this
and I'm basically Win Metawin.

129
00:07:20,901 --> 00:07:22,370
The audacity.

130
00:07:22,503 --> 00:07:23,590
If I get more handsome

131
00:07:23,615 --> 00:07:25,568
and people start flirting
and checking me out,

132
00:07:25,899 --> 00:07:26,899
won't you be jealous?

133
00:07:26,924 --> 00:07:28,400
I want to be jealous sometimes.

134
00:07:29,161 --> 00:07:30,161
Can I?

135
00:07:40,207 --> 00:07:41,207
Ugh.

136
00:07:41,432 --> 00:07:43,018
Classic soap opera interruption.

137
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:44,338
Who is it?

138
00:07:44,977 --> 00:07:45,977
It's Pailin.

139
00:07:46,984 --> 00:07:48,424
I'll wait outside.

140
00:07:58,261 --> 00:07:58,937
What's up?

141
00:07:58,981 --> 00:08:00,120
(What's up, bestie?)

142
00:08:00,217 --> 00:08:01,217
(What are you doing?)

143
00:08:02,542 --> 00:08:04,329
You called right on time.

144
00:08:04,479 --> 00:08:06,480
I brought Toto to the gym.

145
00:08:06,917 --> 00:08:07,917
(Oh.)

146
00:08:08,109 --> 00:08:09,640
(What a sporty couple.)

147
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:11,007
(Any love scenes happening?)

148
00:08:11,147 --> 00:08:12,159
(You totally forgot about me.)

149
00:08:12,183 --> 00:08:14,280
If you're calling to
scold me, I'm hanging up.

150
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:15,415
(Wait.)

151
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:17,000
(I was just teasing you a bit.)

152
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:21,380
(I just wanted to ask if you've heard back
from Magic Sky Airway.)

153
00:08:24,453 --> 00:08:25,320
Yeah.

154
00:08:25,442 --> 00:08:27,600
But I haven't told Toto.

155
00:08:27,778 --> 00:08:30,360
(What? Why haven't you told him?)

156
00:08:31,634 --> 00:08:34,534
I'll just tell him if I
actually get the job.

157
00:08:35,089 --> 00:08:37,480
(Come on. It might become a problem.)

158
00:08:39,521 --> 00:08:40,652
I know.

159
00:08:41,164 --> 00:08:42,173
I have to go.

160
00:08:49,175 --> 00:08:50,175
Come on!

161
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:52,599
Dribble faster.

162
00:08:52,931 --> 00:08:54,080
Dribble properly. Next one.

163
00:08:55,014 --> 00:08:56,440
Faster. What even is that jump?

164
00:08:58,130 --> 00:08:59,472
Goalie, keep moving.

165
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:00,554
Let's see some footwork.

166
00:09:00,818 --> 00:09:01,874
Come on, last one!

167
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:07,087
Let's take a break here.

168
00:09:07,136 --> 00:09:09,116
Hello, new P.E. teacher.

169
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:11,442
Oh. What brings you here?

170
00:09:11,826 --> 00:09:12,826
I took a bus.

171
00:09:12,883 --> 00:09:13,883
Okay.

172
00:09:14,203 --> 00:09:15,683
Throwing my own joke back at me, huh?

173
00:09:17,477 --> 00:09:18,527
I got you some snacks.

174
00:09:20,113 --> 00:09:21,113
Thank you.

175
00:09:28,257 --> 00:09:29,627
I'm surprised you know
I love pandan pancakes.

176
00:09:29,651 --> 00:09:31,400
I've been paying attention for years.

177
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:38,913
Now that I see you in the P.E. uniform,
I can't help but worry.

178
00:09:39,668 --> 00:09:40,604
Worry about what?

179
00:09:40,669 --> 00:09:42,647
I worry about the kids
who'll have a crush on you.

180
00:09:43,312 --> 00:09:44,432
You know what?

181
00:09:44,807 --> 00:09:46,160
A P.E. teacher like you

182
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:48,360
is the main reason kids turn gay.

183
00:09:51,304 --> 00:09:54,780
So, how's your first day of teaching?

184
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:57,532
I haven't really gotten the hang of it yet.

185
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,160
Being a teacher isn't easy at all.

186
00:09:59,317 --> 00:10:00,400
You need patience.

187
00:10:00,677 --> 00:10:03,063
Playing and teaching
are different skill sets.

188
00:10:03,419 --> 00:10:05,040
You can take your time.

189
00:10:05,599 --> 00:10:06,760
But what I know for sure is

190
00:10:07,043 --> 00:10:10,080
your talent can definitely help the kids.

191
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:15,080
Will you come watch me every day?

192
00:10:16,596 --> 00:10:20,215
Sorry, but I have a job to do.

193
00:10:20,447 --> 00:10:22,203
I'm not free like when I was in grade 10.

194
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:25,340
I need emotional support.

195
00:10:25,423 --> 00:10:27,840
How about you quit being a flight attendant

196
00:10:28,323 --> 00:10:30,120
and become an English teacher here?

197
00:10:30,393 --> 00:10:34,080
So we can be the school's
hot teacher couple.

198
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,280
No.

199
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:41,862
Being a cheerleader is what I do best.

200
00:10:48,562 --> 00:10:49,600
What are you doing?

201
00:10:49,671 --> 00:10:50,720
The kids saw that.

202
00:10:50,798 --> 00:10:52,240
I couldn't stop myself.

203
00:10:53,756 --> 00:10:55,920
Come on. You're a teacher.

204
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:57,723
You need to be a good role model
for the kids.

205
00:10:57,747 --> 00:10:59,040
I am being a good role model.

206
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:00,340
How am I not?

207
00:11:03,562 --> 00:11:05,560
Coach, should we practice?

208
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:07,068
You two can save the romance for later.

209
00:11:07,092 --> 00:11:08,612
We're jealous here.

210
00:11:09,859 --> 00:11:10,975
Hurry up, Coach.

211
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,120
Stop flirting.

212
00:11:13,568 --> 00:11:15,012
See? I told you.

213
00:11:16,106 --> 00:11:17,760
You guys are in for a rough time.

214
00:11:18,074 --> 00:11:19,074
Go.

215
00:11:19,963 --> 00:11:20,963
Go now.

216
00:11:35,473 --> 00:11:36,183
Come on.

217
00:11:36,231 --> 00:11:37,508
Come on, To!

218
00:11:37,806 --> 00:11:40,339
You know what? If I weren't a rescuer,

219
00:11:40,612 --> 00:11:42,332
View Kunlavut wouldn't even stand a chance.

220
00:11:42,371 --> 00:11:43,521
I'd smash the net to shreds.

221
00:11:43,546 --> 00:11:44,331
Whoa.

222
00:11:44,442 --> 00:11:45,175
You know why?

223
00:11:45,237 --> 00:11:45,774
You know why?

224
00:11:45,799 --> 00:11:46,627
Don't tell me…

225
00:11:46,652 --> 00:11:47,360
It's because…

226
00:11:47,426 --> 00:11:49,144
Everything Toto.

227
00:11:51,645 --> 00:11:52,480
Everything what?

228
00:11:52,505 --> 00:11:53,960
Everything Toto.

229
00:11:55,613 --> 00:11:56,257
Come on.

230
00:11:56,298 --> 00:11:56,978
Serve it up.

231
00:11:57,003 --> 00:11:58,003
Come on.

232
00:11:59,253 --> 00:12:00,253
Hey.

233
00:12:01,306 --> 00:12:02,306
Ouch!

234
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:06,624
Hey.

235
00:12:13,641 --> 00:12:14,446
Namo Toto.

236
00:12:14,471 --> 00:12:15,298
Fall hard for Toto.

237
00:12:15,323 --> 00:12:16,200
Heal this bump.

238
00:12:16,313 --> 00:12:17,313
Poof!

239
00:12:18,104 --> 00:12:19,104
All better.

240
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:20,267
Better now?

241
00:12:20,632 --> 00:12:21,632
All better.

242
00:12:21,939 --> 00:12:22,660
Enough.

243
00:12:22,747 --> 00:12:23,560
There, that's one.

244
00:12:23,762 --> 00:12:26,480
You don't have to baby me like this.

245
00:12:26,867 --> 00:12:29,040
I have to take care of you,
not the other way around.

246
00:12:29,439 --> 00:12:30,439
Really?

247
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:34,280
What are you wearing?

248
00:12:34,768 --> 00:12:36,336
Wow, you got your name embroidered too?

249
00:12:37,411 --> 00:12:40,200
I called and asked your junior
to prepare it for me.

250
00:12:42,924 --> 00:12:44,760
But you make it look so expensive.

251
00:12:44,944 --> 00:12:45,944
Look at me.

252
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:50,760
So, how are you going to
take care of me today?

253
00:12:51,474 --> 00:12:52,474
Here.

254
00:12:53,401 --> 00:12:56,964
I brought some healthy stuff for you.

255
00:12:57,524 --> 00:12:58,793
Salad.

256
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:00,000
Vitamins.

257
00:13:00,152 --> 00:13:01,152
Sunscreen.

258
00:13:03,257 --> 00:13:05,200
Fish.

259
00:13:05,678 --> 00:13:06,880
Fruits.

260
00:13:07,294 --> 00:13:08,197
Grapes.

261
00:13:08,248 --> 00:13:09,319
These are so healthy.

262
00:13:09,398 --> 00:13:10,398
Guava.

263
00:13:12,324 --> 00:13:14,120
And here's a salad dressing.

264
00:13:19,129 --> 00:13:20,720
If you keep doing this for me

265
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,960
and I get used to it, what will you do?

266
00:13:23,690 --> 00:13:24,760
I'm demanding, you know?

267
00:13:26,756 --> 00:13:28,080
I don't only want your heart.

268
00:13:28,898 --> 00:13:29,898
I want your body too.

269
00:13:31,492 --> 00:13:33,360
You're always so wild, aren't you?

270
00:13:35,620 --> 00:13:37,280
Now that I got this for you,

271
00:13:37,856 --> 00:13:40,040
you have to apply it before coming to work.

272
00:13:40,094 --> 00:13:42,320
Apply it on both your face and body.

273
00:13:42,698 --> 00:13:43,359
No.

274
00:13:43,384 --> 00:13:44,260
I want you to apply it for me.

275
00:13:44,401 --> 00:13:45,401
It'll absorb better.

276
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,120
Come on.

277
00:13:48,298 --> 00:13:50,520
Do I have to apply to be a rescuer?

278
00:13:50,709 --> 00:13:53,120
I think I qualify.

279
00:13:53,557 --> 00:13:55,440
I have the skills. You already taught me.

280
00:13:55,814 --> 00:13:57,280
No need. It's exhausting.

281
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:00,267
Your job is exhausting enough.

282
00:14:01,134 --> 00:14:03,400
Being a rescuer takes true passion.

283
00:14:03,899 --> 00:14:05,899
You can't just do it
because you want to please me.

284
00:14:07,628 --> 00:14:09,320
You're better off working in the sky.

285
00:14:10,724 --> 00:14:12,680
Seeing your effort today is enough for me.

286
00:14:16,364 --> 00:14:17,364
It's not enough.

287
00:14:18,381 --> 00:14:19,640
I can do a lot more for you.

288
00:14:21,851 --> 00:14:22,851
Turn around.

289
00:14:23,761 --> 00:14:24,801
Let me give you a massage.

290
00:14:25,286 --> 00:14:26,286
Lean back.

291
00:14:26,917 --> 00:14:27,917
Lie down.

292
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,200
- Really?
- Yeah.

293
00:14:29,343 --> 00:14:30,503
- Here.
- I'm lying down then.

294
00:14:30,586 --> 00:14:31,625
Want some balm?

295
00:14:33,512 --> 00:14:34,570
Can you give me a B to B?

296
00:14:36,055 --> 00:14:38,775
Let's save that for our room.

297
00:14:41,536 --> 00:14:42,780
Then can we go to our room now?

298
00:14:42,924 --> 00:14:43,924
You pervert.

299
00:14:48,499 --> 00:14:50,360
Don't people in a relationship get tired?

300
00:14:50,775 --> 00:14:52,455
They have to be everything for each other.

301
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,480
That's too exhausting.

302
00:14:56,011 --> 00:14:58,080
I'd better stay single without skills.

303
00:15:02,307 --> 00:15:02,968
It hurts!

304
00:15:03,052 --> 00:15:04,165
I'm not even pressing hard.

305
00:15:04,190 --> 00:15:05,190
Just gently.

306
00:15:05,602 --> 00:15:07,606
(Rescue unit needed.)

307
00:15:16,509 --> 00:15:17,560
This will sting a bit.

308
00:15:18,396 --> 00:15:21,000
Good thing the wound on the outside
isn't anything serious.

309
00:15:21,452 --> 00:15:22,920
But you still need a doctor to check it out.

310
00:15:24,608 --> 00:15:27,354
Also, please get a certified helmet.

311
00:15:27,379 --> 00:15:28,400
Don't buy cheap stuff.

312
00:15:28,706 --> 00:15:29,880
Please invest in your life.

313
00:15:29,948 --> 00:15:31,040
Yes, sir.

314
00:15:31,832 --> 00:15:32,520
Hey.

315
00:15:32,683 --> 00:15:34,320
Stop lecturing him. He's in pain.

316
00:15:35,004 --> 00:15:36,244
Let's take him to the hospital.

317
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:38,320
Help me lift him.

318
00:15:38,670 --> 00:15:41,400
Wow, you're giving me orders now?

319
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,040
Yes, darling.

320
00:15:45,526 --> 00:15:47,040
Oh, you two are dating?

321
00:15:47,598 --> 00:15:49,440
A rescuer couple.

322
00:15:49,465 --> 00:15:51,040
Working together.

323
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:53,195
Love among bloodstains.

324
00:15:53,929 --> 00:15:54,895
Still got a smart mouth, huh?

325
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:56,109
Get on by yourself, then.

326
00:15:56,431 --> 00:15:57,431
I can't.

327
00:15:58,364 --> 00:15:59,364
Let's go.

328
00:15:59,639 --> 00:16:00,639
Come on.

329
00:16:01,601 --> 00:16:03,041
- One. Two. Three.
- One. Two. Three.

330
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:25,084
What are you doing?

331
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:26,709
I don't even know what tired is anymore.

332
00:16:27,642 --> 00:16:28,388
Go.

333
00:16:28,421 --> 00:16:29,621
The injured person is waiting.

334
00:16:44,656 --> 00:16:45,720
Tomorrow is your day off.

335
00:16:46,131 --> 00:16:47,451
Do you want to stay over tonight?

336
00:16:47,714 --> 00:16:49,000
So we can spend time together.

337
00:16:49,359 --> 00:16:50,120
Sure.

338
00:16:50,307 --> 00:16:52,080
Do you want to go out tomorrow?

339
00:16:52,436 --> 00:16:53,436
Let's go.

340
00:16:53,490 --> 00:16:55,290
We can go to the temple
to pray for blessings

341
00:16:56,337 --> 00:16:57,813
or ask for an auspicious wedding date.

342
00:16:57,837 --> 00:16:58,837
Wedding?

343
00:16:59,876 --> 00:17:01,916
Wow. Do you have the dowry?

344
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:02,760
Yes.

345
00:17:02,844 --> 00:17:03,844
Oh.

346
00:17:04,923 --> 00:17:05,923
Toto.

347
00:17:17,017 --> 00:17:19,466
Why didn't you tell me
you saw Mom recently?

348
00:17:20,845 --> 00:17:22,965
I didn't think it was important,
so I didn't tell you.

349
00:17:34,483 --> 00:17:37,043
Lew, can you put the laundry in the machine
and start it for me?

350
00:17:37,541 --> 00:17:38,424
I've already washed everything.

351
00:17:38,507 --> 00:17:39,507
Not yet.

352
00:17:39,593 --> 00:17:40,760
There's my laundry too.

353
00:17:49,292 --> 00:17:50,060
Hello.

354
00:17:50,085 --> 00:17:52,762
- Hi.
- I'm Kanit. Toto's boyfriend.

355
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:53,947
Oh, really?

356
00:17:54,454 --> 00:17:55,600
You're good-looking.

357
00:17:56,828 --> 00:17:57,828
You look good together.

358
00:17:58,037 --> 00:17:58,800
Thank you.

359
00:17:58,828 --> 00:18:00,640
Toto hasn't told me anything.

360
00:18:05,671 --> 00:18:08,720
Ignore her.
She won't be back after this.

361
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:25,840
Tonlew said

362
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,200
you've been working hard lately.

363
00:18:30,754 --> 00:18:32,480
I've been working hard my whole life.

364
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,680
One needs to work for money.

365
00:18:38,724 --> 00:18:40,160
I don't want to mooch off anyone.

366
00:18:45,711 --> 00:18:49,120
Tonlew also said you're starting a company.

367
00:18:52,386 --> 00:18:53,048
Can I help?

368
00:18:53,103 --> 00:18:54,103
There's no need.

369
00:18:55,149 --> 00:18:56,989
I've been taking care
of myself my whole life.

370
00:18:57,552 --> 00:18:58,657
I'll find the money.

371
00:19:00,487 --> 00:19:01,920
I know you're angry with me,

372
00:19:03,407 --> 00:19:04,920
but can't you give me a chance?

373
00:19:05,827 --> 00:19:08,280
People make mistakes in life.

374
00:19:08,930 --> 00:19:10,767
So you're trying to make it up
by throwing money at me?

375
00:19:10,791 --> 00:19:11,791
Go ahead.

376
00:19:13,091 --> 00:19:14,440
Yell at me all you want.

377
00:19:17,203 --> 00:19:18,443
But can you please accept this?

378
00:19:18,507 --> 00:19:19,552
Whose money is that?

379
00:19:19,578 --> 00:19:20,630
Your husband's again?

380
00:19:23,577 --> 00:19:24,920
If you don't care about yourself,

381
00:19:25,036 --> 00:19:26,410
at least think about your sister.

382
00:19:27,954 --> 00:19:29,120
I guess this is all I can do.

383
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,395
You're just doing this
to make yourself feel better.

384
00:19:53,312 --> 00:19:54,920
You don't care about Lew and me.

385
00:20:38,178 --> 00:20:39,440
Still thinking about your mom?

386
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:44,395
I don't want to accept her money.

387
00:20:45,034 --> 00:20:46,676
I don't want to owe her anything anymore.

388
00:20:47,906 --> 00:20:49,040
I understand you.

389
00:20:50,215 --> 00:20:52,920
You have every right
to be angry with your mom.

390
00:20:53,619 --> 00:20:55,760
And I won't say anything
to change your mind.

391
00:20:56,948 --> 00:21:02,200
But about your company,
I have some money.

392
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:03,957
Do you want to use it for now?

393
00:21:03,982 --> 00:21:04,982
No.

394
00:21:06,127 --> 00:21:07,440
I don't want to trouble you.

395
00:21:09,403 --> 00:21:11,120
You have your own expenses.

396
00:21:11,171 --> 00:21:12,953
Not anymore. I already bought the condo.

397
00:21:14,123 --> 00:21:17,180
Besides, I've been wanting
to invest my money anyway.

398
00:21:18,214 --> 00:21:22,400
I think your start-up has
the potential to go far.

399
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,045
What do you mean?

400
00:21:28,319 --> 00:21:30,280
If you don't want to borrow my money,

401
00:21:31,060 --> 00:21:32,780
how about you let me
invest in your company?

402
00:21:33,786 --> 00:21:35,617
I'll be investing in
something I believe in.

403
00:21:36,593 --> 00:21:38,720
And I believe you can become a frontrunner.

404
00:21:39,768 --> 00:21:40,785
Just go for it.

405
00:21:43,522 --> 00:21:45,000
It'll be our success.

406
00:21:51,470 --> 00:21:52,718
Are you sure it's a good idea?

407
00:21:53,946 --> 00:21:57,760
They say running a business
with your partner is a breakup risk.

408
00:22:00,219 --> 00:22:02,476
Let them talk. I don't care.

409
00:22:04,048 --> 00:22:05,440
I only care about how you feel.

410
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:20,920
No one has ever believed in me this much
in my entire life.

411
00:22:51,916 --> 00:22:52,916
Hey, Beer.

412
00:22:55,763 --> 00:22:56,800
You're handsome, bro.

413
00:22:57,132 --> 00:22:58,132
As always.

414
00:22:58,346 --> 00:22:59,920
Why? Where are you going?

415
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:02,750
I'm going to pick up my boyfriend
from the airport.

416
00:23:02,829 --> 00:23:04,429
Pick up your boyfriend from the airport?

417
00:23:05,582 --> 00:23:06,582
Do you have a roll-on?

418
00:23:07,008 --> 00:23:08,080
Can I borrow it?

419
00:23:09,366 --> 00:23:10,470
You should start carrying your own.

420
00:23:10,494 --> 00:23:11,128
Go buy one.

421
00:23:11,153 --> 00:23:12,365
And you should buy a new one.

422
00:23:12,447 --> 00:23:13,800
Look, it's literally bubbling.

423
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,880
Oh, by the way,
someone sent you a letter this morning.

424
00:23:17,376 --> 00:23:18,383
What letter?

425
00:23:18,494 --> 00:23:20,920
Looks like one of those donation envelopes.

426
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:21,980
Really?

427
00:23:22,099 --> 00:23:23,051
Can you put my money in?

428
00:23:23,103 --> 00:23:24,103
Sure.

429
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:26,640
Want a smack?

430
00:23:26,767 --> 00:23:27,767
Why so aggressive?

431
00:23:28,308 --> 00:23:29,454
Who knows what letter it is?

432
00:23:29,946 --> 00:23:31,320
Look at you all dressed up though.

433
00:23:48,698 --> 00:23:49,799
I think this one is good.

434
00:23:50,357 --> 00:23:52,437
It's decent enough to work in
and not very expensive.

435
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:53,720
Try it.

436
00:23:58,177 --> 00:23:59,857
What do you think? Good?

437
00:24:00,966 --> 00:24:03,280
Why? You want me to review this chair?

438
00:24:03,428 --> 00:24:04,428
Mm.

439
00:24:05,428 --> 00:24:06,428
Well…

440
00:24:06,499 --> 00:24:08,400
Now I'm hooked after trying it.

441
00:24:08,986 --> 00:24:10,866
I can sit for a long time
without feeling sore.

442
00:24:10,936 --> 00:24:11,837
It stays hard.

443
00:24:11,862 --> 00:24:12,862
Pure bliss.

444
00:24:13,508 --> 00:24:15,181
You're starting to get as wild as me.

445
00:24:15,303 --> 00:24:18,631
Oh, it's always been in me.

446
00:24:18,666 --> 00:24:20,600
You just woke it up.

447
00:24:21,872 --> 00:24:22,952
Try sitting in it for real.

448
00:24:26,337 --> 00:24:27,337
Good?

449
00:24:27,513 --> 00:24:28,513
Hey.

450
00:24:29,207 --> 00:24:30,240
Won't this break easily?

451
00:24:30,379 --> 00:24:30,963
Really?

452
00:24:30,988 --> 00:24:31,464
Yeah.

453
00:24:31,489 --> 00:24:34,543
Why don't we invest in one that lasts?

454
00:24:34,591 --> 00:24:36,850
That way, it'll be worth it.
A long-term investment.

455
00:24:37,914 --> 00:24:39,200
Here. Look.

456
00:24:39,828 --> 00:24:40,828
Here.

457
00:24:41,399 --> 00:24:43,320
This one is an ergonomic chair.

458
00:24:43,549 --> 00:24:44,275
It's good.

459
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:46,863
When you sit for long hours in the office,
it'll save your back.

460
00:24:49,010 --> 00:24:50,850
You can almost buy a motorbike
with this price.

461
00:24:50,913 --> 00:24:51,913
It's so damn expensive.

462
00:24:52,603 --> 00:24:53,419
Come on.

463
00:24:53,444 --> 00:24:55,560
It's a good long-term investment.

464
00:24:55,646 --> 00:24:57,640
Choosing a chair is
like choosing a partner.

465
00:24:57,857 --> 00:25:00,400
You have to choose the one
that's good and expensive

466
00:25:00,508 --> 00:25:01,720
so it'll be worth it.

467
00:25:02,293 --> 00:25:03,353
Let me try it then.

468
00:25:03,436 --> 00:25:04,906
Hey, no.

469
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,496
You're heavy.

470
00:25:08,945 --> 00:25:10,040
I'll get this one.

471
00:25:11,694 --> 00:25:12,814
It's expensive

472
00:25:13,271 --> 00:25:15,189
but soft, comfortable,

473
00:25:15,915 --> 00:25:16,997
and good for the heart.

474
00:25:17,639 --> 00:25:18,920
It won't break easily.

475
00:25:20,061 --> 00:25:21,520
It'll stay with me for life.

476
00:25:23,367 --> 00:25:24,807
Can you afford it?

477
00:25:25,026 --> 00:25:26,600
I'll pay in installments.

478
00:25:29,666 --> 00:25:30,666
Ahh!

479
00:25:33,139 --> 00:25:34,499
I'm wheeling this to the register.

480
00:25:43,206 --> 00:25:44,206
Here.

481
00:25:44,826 --> 00:25:46,016
Look at this place.

482
00:25:46,109 --> 00:25:50,176
The size is perfect for a starting office.

483
00:25:51,842 --> 00:25:53,280
Do we really need this much?

484
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:55,351
Of course, we do.

485
00:25:55,376 --> 00:25:57,176
You're building a start-up.

486
00:25:57,810 --> 00:25:58,960
It has to be this much.

487
00:25:59,372 --> 00:26:00,872
But I'll be working alone.

488
00:26:01,168 --> 00:26:03,960
Look, you might be working alone now,

489
00:26:03,985 --> 00:26:06,215
but later you'll register your company

490
00:26:06,286 --> 00:26:09,134
and you'll need staff
for the kind of work you do.

491
00:26:09,197 --> 00:26:13,329
When clients start flooding in,
you'll need the space.

492
00:26:13,736 --> 00:26:14,840
Look here.

493
00:26:15,118 --> 00:26:17,506
Right when you open the door,

494
00:26:17,689 --> 00:26:20,589
I'll set up a counter
to welcome the clients.

495
00:26:20,759 --> 00:26:24,880
This will be an area for the staff
to take care of them.

496
00:26:25,054 --> 00:26:26,121
And that room over there

497
00:26:26,193 --> 00:26:27,381
will be the meeting room

498
00:26:27,406 --> 00:26:28,840
so you can plan ahead.

499
00:26:29,087 --> 00:26:30,127
I understand,

500
00:26:31,132 --> 00:26:34,880
but I think this is a
little too big for my start.

501
00:26:35,364 --> 00:26:39,000
Hey, you have me as your partner.

502
00:26:40,079 --> 00:26:41,079
I know.

503
00:26:41,707 --> 00:26:46,048
But I want my first office
to feel a bit more like me.

504
00:26:46,691 --> 00:26:48,051
Like a shophouse.

505
00:26:48,714 --> 00:26:50,486
Hmm, that actually makes sense.

506
00:26:50,511 --> 00:26:53,400
We might reach more locals that way.

507
00:26:53,425 --> 00:26:56,960
Yeah, and we can always
think about expanding later.

508
00:26:57,357 --> 00:26:59,712
We can even have a 10-storey building
when the time comes.

509
00:27:01,103 --> 00:27:02,362
You'll be the president

510
00:27:02,446 --> 00:27:04,560
and CEO of Everything Toto.

511
00:27:05,870 --> 00:27:07,550
And what's your role?

512
00:27:10,503 --> 00:27:11,703
I'm yours, CEO.

513
00:27:13,338 --> 00:27:15,000
I can be anything you want me to be.

514
00:27:16,793 --> 00:27:18,320
We'll be each other's future.

515
00:27:33,780 --> 00:27:36,560
Hey, if I weren't a flight attendant,

516
00:27:37,002 --> 00:27:39,800
we'd have more cozy
time like this together.

517
00:27:42,592 --> 00:27:44,176
Soon, when we work together,

518
00:27:45,041 --> 00:27:46,605
we'll always be sweet like this.

519
00:27:47,250 --> 00:27:48,983
We could go at it any way,

520
00:27:49,472 --> 00:27:50,472
anywhere,

521
00:27:50,566 --> 00:27:51,760
and anytime we want.

522
00:27:53,662 --> 00:27:54,971
I guess we won't get to work.

523
00:27:55,304 --> 00:27:57,320
Oh, we can work while we eat.

524
00:27:58,365 --> 00:27:59,365
Here.

525
00:28:04,389 --> 00:28:05,240
Mango?

526
00:28:05,388 --> 00:28:06,240
Go ahead and eat it.

527
00:28:06,332 --> 00:28:07,400
I want you to eat it.

528
00:28:11,359 --> 00:28:12,440
This mango is good.

529
00:28:12,954 --> 00:28:14,196
I want more mangos.

530
00:28:14,297 --> 00:28:15,417
It's all gone.

531
00:28:15,528 --> 00:28:16,840
Can you get more as a topping?

532
00:28:18,932 --> 00:28:19,983
Let me go get some more.

533
00:28:21,389 --> 00:28:22,720
When you're Toto's boyfriend,

534
00:28:22,764 --> 00:28:24,240
you get to eat everything you want.

535
00:28:24,311 --> 00:28:25,520
You want to eat mango?

536
00:28:25,605 --> 00:28:26,925
I'll bring a whole garden to you.

537
00:28:39,233 --> 00:28:40,233
Oh!

538
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:49,788
HEY, I MADE IT INTO MAGIC SKY AIRWAY.

539
00:28:53,633 --> 00:28:54,633
Damn.

540
00:29:09,931 --> 00:29:10,760
Coming right up.

541
00:29:10,882 --> 00:29:12,682
Mango for Toto's boyfriend.

542
00:29:14,338 --> 00:29:15,338
Thank you.

543
00:29:16,128 --> 00:29:17,128
Come on.

544
00:29:17,531 --> 00:29:18,680
It's a whole mango.

545
00:29:19,316 --> 00:29:20,251
Let me feed you.

546
00:29:20,276 --> 00:29:21,440
Wow.

547
00:29:24,250 --> 00:29:25,184
How is it?

548
00:29:25,209 --> 00:29:26,209
Mm.

549
00:29:26,719 --> 00:29:27,719
It's good.

550
00:29:28,149 --> 00:29:28,880
Eat more.

551
00:29:28,905 --> 00:29:29,933
Eat it with this.

552
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:38,468
SUVARNABHUMI AIRPORT

553
00:29:45,616 --> 00:29:46,616
Hey, Ki.

554
00:29:47,147 --> 00:29:49,067
Why did you come pick me up
at the airport today?

555
00:29:50,934 --> 00:29:51,997
I wanted to see you.

556
00:29:52,517 --> 00:29:53,540
I wanted to talk to you.

557
00:29:55,456 --> 00:29:56,496
What's wrong?

558
00:29:57,080 --> 00:29:58,840
Why do you look like
you just got chewed out?

559
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:16,900
LETTER FROM MILITARY

560
00:30:20,674 --> 00:30:21,674
This is…

561
00:30:22,593 --> 00:30:24,232
I have to report for the military draft.

562
00:30:24,816 --> 00:30:26,016
If I'm unlucky,

563
00:30:26,567 --> 00:30:28,241
I'll be stuck in the army for two years.

564
00:30:33,561 --> 00:30:36,160
You won't get drafted.
People will volunteer.

565
00:30:37,587 --> 00:30:38,627
I don't know.

566
00:30:39,942 --> 00:30:43,040
But if I do get drafted, I'll have to
completely overhaul my life plans.

567
00:30:48,211 --> 00:30:49,438
Don't overthink it.

568
00:30:50,652 --> 00:30:52,240
You won't be that unlucky.

569
00:30:53,827 --> 00:30:55,143
Even if you get drafted,

570
00:30:56,214 --> 00:30:57,840
we can still figure it out together.

571
00:30:58,988 --> 00:30:59,988
Right?

572
00:31:06,226 --> 00:31:07,226
Damn it!

573
00:31:08,071 --> 00:31:09,334
Why now?

574
00:31:10,636 --> 00:31:12,000
Right when I got a boyfriend.

575
00:31:16,898 --> 00:31:17,898
Oh, Ki.

576
00:31:18,731 --> 00:31:22,160
If love has no obstacles,
it wouldn't be romantic.

577
00:31:24,957 --> 00:31:25,957
Right?

578
00:31:31,239 --> 00:31:32,239
Don't worry.

579
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:38,783
CLOSED TODAY FOR A PRIVATE EVENT

580
00:31:38,807 --> 00:31:39,912
Where are you taking me, Lew?

581
00:31:39,936 --> 00:31:41,160
We're almost there.

582
00:31:41,261 --> 00:31:42,781
Hold onto me tight.

583
00:31:42,899 --> 00:31:43,899
Don't worry.

584
00:31:44,262 --> 00:31:45,942
Sit down and I'll take off your blindfold.

585
00:31:46,782 --> 00:31:47,653
Where do I sit?

586
00:31:47,678 --> 00:31:48,678
Careful.

587
00:31:50,084 --> 00:31:51,535
Okay. Can you take it off now?

588
00:31:51,642 --> 00:31:52,642
Alright.

589
00:31:55,301 --> 00:32:00,040
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

590
00:32:02,531 --> 00:32:03,558
Is it my birthday?

591
00:32:05,503 --> 00:32:06,503
Damn.

592
00:32:06,959 --> 00:32:08,960
I've been working so
hard I lost track of time.

593
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:10,847
Thank you so much, guys.

594
00:32:10,896 --> 00:32:14,920
And not just your birthday,
we're celebrating your new company too!

595
00:32:17,434 --> 00:32:20,800
We've booked your favorite artist.

596
00:32:21,229 --> 00:32:22,229
Who?

597
00:32:26,907 --> 00:32:28,027
Give it up for.

598
00:32:28,195 --> 00:32:29,440
LOSO!

599
00:32:29,465 --> 00:32:30,465
What?

600
00:32:30,728 --> 00:32:31,728
Really?

601
00:32:32,016 --> 00:32:33,105
Are you serious?

602
00:32:49,660 --> 00:32:52,432
♪ If life is a struggle ♪

603
00:32:53,488 --> 00:32:56,920
♪ One must be able to keep going ♪

604
00:32:57,442 --> 00:33:00,880
♪ Know what's in your heart ♪

605
00:33:01,414 --> 00:33:04,360
♪ Make sure you get there at last ♪

606
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:08,745
♪ Because life is a fight ♪

607
00:33:09,599 --> 00:33:12,360
♪ Learn with all your might ♪

608
00:33:13,457 --> 00:33:16,196
♪ No matter how far the journey is ♪

609
00:33:17,392 --> 00:33:20,451
♪ Only dreamers could make it ♪

610
00:33:20,721 --> 00:33:22,401
♪ I'm one of the people ♪

611
00:33:23,333 --> 00:33:25,243
♪ Fighting this battle ♪

612
00:33:25,439 --> 00:33:28,470
♪ With the great power of faith ♪

613
00:33:28,759 --> 00:33:30,360
♪ Equal start ♪

614
00:33:31,117 --> 00:33:32,946
♪ And same baseline ♪

615
00:33:33,358 --> 00:33:34,958
♪ Ready your heart ♪

616
00:33:35,107 --> 00:33:37,584
♪ Keep it steadfast ♪

617
00:33:38,683 --> 00:33:41,160
♪ Just dare to dream high ♪

618
00:33:41,262 --> 00:33:44,840
♪ And make it come alive ♪

619
00:33:46,978 --> 00:33:48,920
♪ Be confident ♪

620
00:33:49,254 --> 00:33:53,083
♪ You're on the right track ♪

621
00:33:55,130 --> 00:33:56,930
♪ Block the noise outside ♪

622
00:33:57,101 --> 00:34:00,520
♪ Pay it no mind, keep the fire within ♪

623
00:34:00,588 --> 00:34:05,171
♪ Only the determined will win ♪

624
00:34:08,321 --> 00:34:09,428
Hey, is it over already?

625
00:34:09,571 --> 00:34:10,515
Hold up!

626
00:34:10,592 --> 00:34:11,699
Can we sing the hook again?

627
00:34:12,286 --> 00:34:13,800
Please, sing the hook one more time.

628
00:34:13,973 --> 00:34:14,973
Come on.

629
00:34:15,193 --> 00:34:21,680
♪ Just dare to dream high
and make it come alive ♪

630
00:34:23,916 --> 00:34:29,120
♪ Be confident, you're on the right track ♪

631
00:34:38,763 --> 00:34:41,640
Magic Sky Airway will be proud.

632
00:34:41,974 --> 00:34:45,120
When my friend moves to Dubai,
I'll definitely miss him.

633
00:34:48,057 --> 00:34:49,091
Who's going to Dubai?

634
00:34:50,212 --> 00:34:52,680
Oh? Kanit, of course.

635
00:34:52,782 --> 00:34:54,640
He got his new wings for Dubai.

636
00:35:25,124 --> 00:35:26,124
Come on.

637
00:35:26,323 --> 00:35:28,257
You forgot your own birthday.

638
00:35:28,635 --> 00:35:30,640
I had to ask Tonlew.

639
00:35:31,232 --> 00:35:34,040
What do you think of my surprise?

640
00:35:34,353 --> 00:35:35,061
You like it?

641
00:35:35,107 --> 00:35:36,327
I put so much effort into this, you know?

642
00:35:36,351 --> 00:35:39,760
I had to recruit Je Zo and Beer's help.

643
00:35:40,715 --> 00:35:44,240
Am I cool enough to join your gang now?

644
00:35:55,226 --> 00:35:56,226
Oh.

645
00:35:57,297 --> 00:35:58,841
What's wrong?

646
00:35:58,941 --> 00:36:00,320
Are you stunned? You're so quiet.

647
00:36:02,226 --> 00:36:03,314
Why didn't you tell me?

648
00:36:04,139 --> 00:36:05,259
Tell you what?

649
00:36:07,919 --> 00:36:10,359
That you got a job with a new airline
and have to move abroad.

650
00:36:20,037 --> 00:36:23,480
Well, I've been meaning to tell you,

651
00:36:23,804 --> 00:36:25,320
but I couldn't find the right time.

652
00:36:27,140 --> 00:36:28,480
I didn't want you to overthink.

653
00:36:29,499 --> 00:36:31,179
Of course, I'd overthink.

654
00:36:32,062 --> 00:36:33,560
But I'm so happy for you.

655
00:36:34,016 --> 00:36:35,800
You made your dream come true.

656
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:38,640
Even if we have to do long-distance.

657
00:36:40,112 --> 00:36:41,112
Come on.

658
00:36:41,553 --> 00:36:43,240
I'm not moving there for good.

659
00:36:43,457 --> 00:36:45,760
It's just for a while, then I'll be back.

660
00:36:46,009 --> 00:36:48,520
But we have so little time for each other
as it is.

661
00:36:54,639 --> 00:36:56,240
If we love each other enough,

662
00:36:57,848 --> 00:36:59,560
no matter how far apart we are,

663
00:37:00,201 --> 00:37:01,520
we can make it work.

664
00:37:06,930 --> 00:37:07,930
Next time,

665
00:37:08,083 --> 00:37:09,600
please tell me things right away.

666
00:37:10,157 --> 00:37:11,757
Don't let me find out from someone else.

667
00:37:14,588 --> 00:37:15,588
I promise.

668
00:37:21,348 --> 00:37:22,800
I'm so proud of you.

669
00:37:26,653 --> 00:37:27,800
Can I ask for one thing?

670
00:37:28,534 --> 00:37:29,534
What is it?

671
00:37:30,077 --> 00:37:31,400
Can you sing for me again?

672
00:37:32,498 --> 00:37:33,498
Again?

673
00:37:38,099 --> 00:37:40,080
♪ Block the noise outside ♪

674
00:37:40,472 --> 00:37:43,880
♪ Pay it no mind, keep the fire within ♪

675
00:37:44,434 --> 00:37:48,880
♪ Only the determined will win ♪

676
00:38:40,562 --> 00:38:42,922
In just a few months,
you'll be wearing a different uniform.

677
00:38:43,416 --> 00:38:45,360
I think I'll miss you in this one.

678
00:38:47,402 --> 00:38:48,522
But it's okay.

679
00:38:48,561 --> 00:38:49,920
I like you in every outfit.

680
00:38:50,017 --> 00:38:51,017
Me too.

681
00:38:51,243 --> 00:38:54,353
Whether you wear white, blue,

682
00:38:54,647 --> 00:38:57,443
or this red fertilizer giveaway shirt,

683
00:38:58,012 --> 00:38:59,040
I like it all.

684
00:38:59,184 --> 00:39:00,680
I don't think it's the outfits.

685
00:39:01,309 --> 00:39:02,360
You just like the person.

686
00:39:05,791 --> 00:39:06,791
Hey.

687
00:39:07,449 --> 00:39:08,007
Hmm?

688
00:39:08,047 --> 00:39:10,080
I haven't gotten you a gift yet.

689
00:39:11,121 --> 00:39:12,444
You don't have to.

690
00:39:12,583 --> 00:39:13,583
Come on.

691
00:39:13,774 --> 00:39:17,806
Having you as my boyfriend
is the most precious gift in my life.

692
00:39:19,242 --> 00:39:21,120
Oh, you're always so dramatic.

693
00:39:21,372 --> 00:39:23,800
But I'll buy you a gift anyway.

694
00:39:24,394 --> 00:39:26,261
How about I take you to join

695
00:39:26,887 --> 00:39:28,520
the Mile High Club?

696
00:39:30,001 --> 00:39:31,001
What's that?

697
00:39:32,076 --> 00:39:34,320
Well, that means…

698
00:39:34,863 --> 00:39:38,781
We're going to do it on the plane.

699
00:39:41,843 --> 00:39:42,843
I'm in.

700
00:39:42,890 --> 00:39:43,890
I like it.

701
00:39:43,953 --> 00:39:45,000
That's exciting.

702
00:39:45,881 --> 00:39:46,695
How about this flight?

703
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:48,308
- Let's go.
- Stop. Are you crazy?

704
00:39:48,333 --> 00:39:49,360
I'm just kidding.

705
00:39:52,263 --> 00:39:55,920
I'm glad we're growing on our own paths.

706
00:39:58,533 --> 00:40:00,280
And I appreciate your support.

707
00:40:06,067 --> 00:40:07,640
Let's succeed together.

708
00:40:10,777 --> 00:40:11,840
I'm going then.

709
00:40:21,206 --> 00:40:22,206
Hey!

710
00:40:25,376 --> 00:40:26,440
Did you forget something?

711
00:40:42,889 --> 00:40:44,005
You forgot that.

712
00:40:46,313 --> 00:40:47,480
See you when you're back.

713
00:40:47,706 --> 00:40:48,706
Mm.

714
00:41:05,094 --> 00:41:06,094
Here.

715
00:41:06,169 --> 00:41:07,190
This is Phra Boonrod.

716
00:41:07,555 --> 00:41:08,595
Super sacred.

717
00:41:09,682 --> 00:41:11,102
Put it in your mouth before you draw.

718
00:41:11,126 --> 00:41:12,160
You'll survive. Trust me.

719
00:41:17,061 --> 00:41:17,880
Hey!

720
00:41:17,914 --> 00:41:18,688
You're supposed to blow on the head.

721
00:41:18,713 --> 00:41:19,753
- That's spit!
- Come on.

722
00:41:19,944 --> 00:41:20,944
It's sacred.

723
00:41:22,049 --> 00:41:22,837
Bro.

724
00:41:23,064 --> 00:41:23,894
You're definitely getting drafted.

725
00:41:23,943 --> 00:41:24,943
What the hell?

726
00:41:28,238 --> 00:41:29,440
There are so many volunteers.

727
00:41:29,687 --> 00:41:30,840
You'll be safe.

728
00:41:41,437 --> 00:41:42,437
Black!

729
00:41:42,857 --> 00:41:44,320
I'm safe, Mom!

730
00:41:44,723 --> 00:41:46,600
Number 107.

731
00:41:47,771 --> 00:41:48,771
Red! Red!

732
00:41:48,832 --> 00:41:50,065
Red! Red!

733
00:41:51,903 --> 00:41:52,600
Black!

734
00:41:52,627 --> 00:41:53,627
Yay!

735
00:41:59,816 --> 00:42:00,446
Red!

736
00:42:00,471 --> 00:42:01,880
Army, Batch 1!

737
00:42:06,637 --> 00:42:07,951
- Black!
- Red!

738
00:42:07,976 --> 00:42:08,778
- Black!
- Red!

739
00:42:08,803 --> 00:42:09,803
Black! Black!

740
00:42:11,802 --> 00:42:12,478
Red!

741
00:42:12,510 --> 00:42:14,040
Army, Batch 1!

742
00:42:15,561 --> 00:42:16,361
Are you scared?

743
00:42:16,386 --> 00:42:17,402
Based on statistics,

744
00:42:17,442 --> 00:42:18,694
red shows up less than three times.

745
00:42:18,718 --> 00:42:20,232
The next one is going to be black.

746
00:42:20,294 --> 00:42:21,600
I'd even bet my house on it.

747
00:42:21,770 --> 00:42:22,770
Trust me. It'll be black.

748
00:42:22,887 --> 00:42:23,887
It's black for sure.

749
00:42:25,542 --> 00:42:27,360
Number 121.

750
00:42:33,128 --> 00:42:34,280
You got this, Ki!

751
00:42:37,978 --> 00:42:38,978
Black! Red!

752
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,760
Black! Red!

753
00:42:40,785 --> 00:42:42,031
Red! Black!

754
00:42:42,170 --> 00:42:43,210
Black! Black!

755
00:42:43,267 --> 00:42:44,267
Black!

756
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:45,767
Red!

757
00:42:45,792 --> 00:42:46,792
It has to be red!

758
00:42:46,823 --> 00:42:47,245
Black!

759
00:42:47,270 --> 00:42:48,270
Come on.

760
00:42:48,528 --> 00:42:49,360
It's definitely red!

761
00:42:49,389 --> 00:42:50,389
Black!

762
00:43:09,564 --> 00:43:10,564
Red!

763
00:43:10,694 --> 00:43:12,440
Army, Batch 1!

764
00:43:13,610 --> 00:43:14,610
Red!

765
00:43:14,677 --> 00:43:15,723
It's red, bro!

766
00:43:16,683 --> 00:43:17,896
Why the hell are you cheering?

767
00:43:17,997 --> 00:43:19,200
Red means he got drafted.

768
00:43:19,456 --> 00:43:20,640
Oh, shit.

769
00:43:20,872 --> 00:43:21,600
Go.

770
00:43:21,704 --> 00:43:23,680
Oh, shit.

771
00:43:30,239 --> 00:43:32,880
We just got together, and now
we have to be apart from each other.

772
00:43:37,097 --> 00:43:38,097
I'm sorry.

773
00:43:39,665 --> 00:43:41,705
I should've done military reserve training
in school

774
00:43:41,923 --> 00:43:45,023
instead of focusing on football,
which got me nowhere in the end.

775
00:43:45,167 --> 00:43:46,720
Don't blame yourself.

776
00:43:47,554 --> 00:43:48,562
No one could've known.

777
00:43:48,628 --> 00:43:49,668
I'm so upset.

778
00:43:50,397 --> 00:43:51,800
I just became a teacher.

779
00:43:53,144 --> 00:43:55,024
I'm just three months away
from getting tenured.

780
00:43:55,981 --> 00:43:58,696
I don't even know what I'll be like
when I get out of the military.

781
00:44:05,294 --> 00:44:06,294
It's okay.

782
00:44:08,055 --> 00:44:09,360
When you get out,

783
00:44:10,643 --> 00:44:12,040
we'll figure it out together.

784
00:44:14,519 --> 00:44:16,440
Life isn't as hopeless as it seems.

785
00:44:38,056 --> 00:44:39,840
Hey, where are you going after we land?

786
00:44:40,269 --> 00:44:42,880
I have a boyfriend.
Of course, I'm going to see him.

787
00:44:43,481 --> 00:44:46,321
Yeah, you and your bragging.

788
00:44:46,360 --> 00:44:47,680
I think I'm going shopping.

789
00:44:47,993 --> 00:44:48,979
You're going shopping?

790
00:44:49,016 --> 00:44:49,497
Mm-hmm.

791
00:44:49,522 --> 00:44:52,360
Look at the weather. It's raining
hard. You'll get struck by lightning.

792
00:44:52,633 --> 00:44:55,160
Oh, I'm used to this weather.

793
00:44:55,219 --> 00:44:56,219
Ladies and gentlemen,

794
00:44:56,314 --> 00:44:58,440
we are currently experiencing
some turbulence.

795
00:44:58,750 --> 00:45:00,122
Please remain seated

796
00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:01,506
and fasten your seatbelts immediately.

797
00:45:01,530 --> 00:45:02,850
Hey, it's shaking too much.

798
00:45:02,917 --> 00:45:03,776
Excuse me.

799
00:45:03,858 --> 00:45:06,500
We're experiencing some turbulence.
It's normal.

800
00:45:06,542 --> 00:45:07,455
Please don't worry.

801
00:45:07,519 --> 00:45:10,160
Please fasten your
seatbelts for your safety.

802
00:45:12,748 --> 00:45:14,480
Excuse me, please fasten your seatbelt.

803
00:45:18,870 --> 00:45:19,580
Hey!

804
00:45:19,605 --> 00:45:20,765
I don't think this is normal.

805
00:45:20,845 --> 00:45:21,986
Sir, please have a seat.

806
00:45:22,087 --> 00:45:22,841
Please fasten your seatbelts.

807
00:45:22,866 --> 00:45:23,640
Please stay calm.

808
00:45:23,665 --> 00:45:24,945
Don't panic.

809
00:45:25,756 --> 00:45:26,796
Am I falling?

810
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:37,106
THANK YOU FOR
BEING MY LIFE ADVENTURE.

811
00:45:37,130 --> 00:45:37,832
GO ACHIEVE YOUR DREAMS.

812
00:45:37,857 --> 00:45:40,057
NO MATTER WHERE YOU ARE,
I'LL ALWAYS BE ROOTING FOR YOU.

813
00:46:05,897 --> 00:46:06,897
Hey!

814
00:46:07,176 --> 00:46:08,259
What are you doing?

815
00:46:09,993 --> 00:46:12,160
You scared me. I thought you were a shark.

816
00:46:12,654 --> 00:46:13,520
If I were a shark,

817
00:46:13,545 --> 00:46:14,785
“Sharks love to nibble on you.”

818
00:46:14,903 --> 00:46:16,844
Were you about to say that line?
I see right through you.

819
00:46:16,868 --> 00:46:18,600
You're onto all my cheesy lines.

820
00:46:18,793 --> 00:46:20,200
Are you running around in my heart?

821
00:46:20,317 --> 00:46:20,861
Oh.

822
00:46:20,886 --> 00:46:21,708
Come on.

823
00:46:21,859 --> 00:46:25,080
You still found a way to flirt with me.

824
00:46:25,232 --> 00:46:27,177
Tell you what.

825
00:46:27,427 --> 00:46:28,920
You don't have to flirt anymore

826
00:46:29,230 --> 00:46:32,720
because you already have my body
and heart.

827
00:46:33,473 --> 00:46:34,880
But I still want more.

828
00:46:35,640 --> 00:46:39,320
I'll keep flirting with you and throwing
cheesy lines at you until you're old.

829
00:46:39,486 --> 00:46:40,486
Come on.

830
00:46:40,648 --> 00:46:42,208
It's always like this in the beginning.

831
00:46:42,507 --> 00:46:44,908
Even salty seawater

832
00:46:45,007 --> 00:46:46,480
can become sweet.

833
00:46:49,432 --> 00:46:50,432
Listen.

834
00:46:50,971 --> 00:46:53,560
Even if it's the beginning,
the middle, or the end,

835
00:46:54,980 --> 00:46:56,400
I'll still love you like this.

836
00:46:57,486 --> 00:47:00,920
If a shark comes,
I'll fight it with my bare hands.

837
00:47:01,158 --> 00:47:02,680
I'll beat it until it drowns.

838
00:47:03,599 --> 00:47:05,040
Or if a Tsunami comes,

839
00:47:06,010 --> 00:47:07,600
I'll surf us out of danger.

840
00:47:08,551 --> 00:47:11,084
I'll be here, on standby for you 24/7.

841
00:47:12,312 --> 00:47:13,099
Hey.

842
00:47:13,300 --> 00:47:15,720
Who are you? Aquaman?

843
00:47:16,898 --> 00:47:18,125
I'm Toto.

844
00:47:19,108 --> 00:47:21,062
Toto is your everything.

845
00:47:36,448 --> 00:47:37,448
Are we falling?

846
00:47:37,586 --> 00:47:38,586
No!

847
00:47:43,040 --> 00:47:44,640
Why is it shaking harder?

848
00:47:45,270 --> 00:47:46,600
This isn't normal.

849
00:47:56,599 --> 00:47:57,599
Hey, To.

850
00:47:57,851 --> 00:47:58,851
To.

851
00:48:01,513 --> 00:48:02,513
Let's go.

852
00:48:03,217 --> 00:48:04,800
We need some beer to take the edge off.

853
00:48:05,044 --> 00:48:06,044
We can't.

854
00:48:06,492 --> 00:48:07,240
Why not?

855
00:48:07,322 --> 00:48:08,720
The foundation just called.

856
00:48:15,630 --> 00:48:16,700
What's the latest update?

857
00:48:17,202 --> 00:48:19,648
The plane made an emergency landing
and slid off the runway.

858
00:48:19,673 --> 00:48:21,240
There are injuries and deaths.

859
00:48:21,742 --> 00:48:22,742
People died?

860
00:48:23,193 --> 00:48:24,017
How many?

861
00:48:24,084 --> 00:48:25,200
They reported just one,

862
00:48:25,225 --> 00:48:26,294
but I'm still not sure.

863
00:48:28,422 --> 00:48:29,448
I'm sure he's fine.

864
00:48:31,099 --> 00:48:32,632
I'm not just worried about my partner.

865
00:48:32,844 --> 00:48:34,400
Our job is to worry about everyone.

866
00:48:36,114 --> 00:48:37,960
Ki, Ja-O, let's split
up to help the injured.

867
00:48:37,985 --> 00:48:38,985
Sure.

868
00:48:40,497 --> 00:48:41,497
How are you feeling?

869
00:48:42,341 --> 00:48:43,341
Hey, To!

870
00:48:43,647 --> 00:48:45,640
This person is bleeding so much.

871
00:48:46,648 --> 00:48:47,820
Take him to the hospital now.

872
00:48:53,633 --> 00:48:54,633
Hey!

873
00:48:56,554 --> 00:48:57,554
Sorry.

874
00:49:03,349 --> 00:49:05,252
Tong, have you seen Kanit?

875
00:49:06,377 --> 00:49:07,377
Not at all.

876
00:49:07,732 --> 00:49:08,800
The rescue team is here.

877
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:19,760
You're fine now. You're safe.

878
00:49:23,731 --> 00:49:24,731
Toto!

879
00:49:25,194 --> 00:49:25,896
Toto!

880
00:49:25,947 --> 00:49:26,711
This way, Toto!

881
00:49:26,836 --> 00:49:27,483
Oh.

882
00:49:27,604 --> 00:49:28,200
Hey!

883
00:49:28,295 --> 00:49:28,967
Please check on Kanit.

884
00:49:28,992 --> 00:49:29,838
- His leg is badly hurt.
- Are you okay?

885
00:49:29,863 --> 00:49:31,122
I'm okay. Help him first.

886
00:49:31,222 --> 00:49:32,240
Please come with me.

887
00:49:32,738 --> 00:49:33,738
Excuse me!

888
00:49:35,174 --> 00:49:36,120
Could you please take the injured?

889
00:49:36,193 --> 00:49:37,000
This way.

890
00:49:37,141 --> 00:49:38,141
Thank you.

891
00:49:39,162 --> 00:49:40,162
This way.

892
00:49:40,205 --> 00:49:41,245
Are you okay?

893
00:49:42,150 --> 00:49:43,150
Does your leg hurt?

894
00:49:43,848 --> 00:49:44,848
Let me see.

895
00:49:44,897 --> 00:49:45,917
Be gentle.

896
00:49:46,212 --> 00:49:48,600
I think I hurt it while rushing
to help the passengers.

897
00:49:54,149 --> 00:49:55,520
I thought I lost you.

898
00:49:58,946 --> 00:50:00,240
I thought the same.

899
00:50:01,700 --> 00:50:05,200
When I was on the plane,
your face flashed through my mind.

900
00:50:07,238 --> 00:50:09,103
At the time, I thought,

901
00:50:10,268 --> 00:50:11,720
if I was going to die,

902
00:50:13,391 --> 00:50:14,791
at least I got to kiss you goodbye.

903
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:16,240
Stop saying things like that.

904
00:50:16,859 --> 00:50:19,560
Do you have any idea how worried sick
I was while driving here?

905
00:50:19,984 --> 00:50:21,320
Just the thought of losing you

906
00:50:21,928 --> 00:50:22,960
is more than I can bear.

907
00:50:28,127 --> 00:50:29,360
Easy.

908
00:50:31,970 --> 00:50:33,440
It's okay. I'm here.

909
00:50:38,281 --> 00:50:39,281
It's okay.

910
00:50:51,157 --> 00:50:52,877
(Next Episode)
I'm going to be based abroad.

911
00:50:53,064 --> 00:50:54,064
Are you okay with that?

912
00:50:54,666 --> 00:50:55,920
I'm happy for you.

913
00:50:56,169 --> 00:50:57,360
But I'm worried about you.

914
00:50:57,959 --> 00:50:59,560
You just got into an accident.

915
00:51:00,066 --> 00:51:02,266
I don't want you to go through anything
like that again.

916
00:51:03,143 --> 00:51:04,242
I'll be away for two years.

917
00:51:04,542 --> 00:51:06,048
If you find someone better than me,

918
00:51:06,137 --> 00:51:07,337
you deserve it.

919
00:51:07,607 --> 00:51:09,057
Telling me to find someone else

920
00:51:09,197 --> 00:51:10,321
is so insulting.

921
00:51:11,758 --> 00:51:12,758
Hey!

922
00:51:12,987 --> 00:51:13,987
Sir.

923
00:51:16,823 --> 00:51:18,557
I have a project to pitch.

924
00:51:18,964 --> 00:51:20,640
I'm going to propose to Kanit.

925
00:51:20,823 --> 00:51:22,800
With me, he'll never shed a tear.

926
00:51:23,272 --> 00:51:24,773
But I still don't like it.

927
00:51:25,679 --> 00:51:27,279
The important thing I want to hear about

928
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:28,751
isn't money.

929
00:51:28,999 --> 00:51:30,360
What I want to know is

930
00:51:30,609 --> 00:51:32,647
why it has to be my son Kanit.

